# Smart Traffic System

A prototype adaptive traffic-signal controller with computer-vision based
ambulance and accident detection, plus vehicle-plate tracking across an
8-signal / 2-intersection layout.

## Features
- **Adaptive signal timing** — green time proportional to vehicle count per road
- **Ambulance priority** — HSV flash-pattern detection (red+blue siren lights)
  automatically opens the ambulance's signal and closes the rest
- **Accident detection** — vehicles stationary for >15s flagged automatically;
  manual reports also accepted from the dashboard
- **Plate trail tracking** — every plate captured by every camera is logged
  with timestamp, signal, and state, so a lost/stolen vehicle's path can be
  reconstructed via the dashboard search
- **Manual override** — force-green any signal from the dashboard or Blynk app

## Architecture
```
[4 webcams] → camera.py
              detector.py   (YOLOv8 + HSV ambulance flash)
              ocr.py        (EasyOCR plate reading)
              accident.py   (stationary-vehicle tracker)
                            ↓
              signal_logic.py (rotation, yellow, priority handling)
                            ↓
              communicator.py → ESP32 → 8 signals (16 R+G LEDs)
                            ↓
              database.py → SQLite (plates, events, signal log)
                            ↓
              dashboard.html (Flask /api/*)
                            ←
              Blynk app (manual override on phone)
```

## Files
| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `app.py` | Flask server + background processing loop |
| `camera.py` | Multi-camera capture threads |
| `detector.py` | YOLOv8 vehicle detection + HSV ambulance flash |
| `accident.py` | Stationary-vehicle tracker + manual flags |
| `ocr.py` | EasyOCR Indian plate reading |
| `signal_logic.py` | Signal state machine (rotation, yellow, priorities) |
| `communicator.py` | HTTP POST signal states to ESP32 |
| `database.py` | SQLite logging (plates, events, signals) |
| `dashboard.html` | Web UI |
| `esp32_traffic_controller.ino` | ESP32 firmware (HTTP + Blynk + LEDs) |

## Hardware
- **Laptop / Raspberry Pi** running Python
- **4 USB webcams** (one per monitored road)
- **ESP32 DevKit V1**
- **16 LEDs + 16 × 220Ω resistors** (8 red, 8 green; yellow shown on dashboard only)
- Optional: breadboard, jumper wires, 5V power supply

## Pin Map (ESP32 → LEDs)
| Signal | Red GPIO | Green GPIO |
|---|---|---|
| S1 | 13 | 14 |
| S2 | 27 | 26 |
| S3 | 25 | 33 |
| S4 | 32 | 4  |
| S5 | 16 | 17 |
| S6 | 18 | 19 |
| S7 | 21 | 22 |
| S8 | 23 | 5  |

## Camera → Signal Mapping
Default mapping (edit `CAM_TO_SIGNALS` in `signal_logic.py` to match your layout):
| Camera | Controls |
|---|---|
| Cam 0 (North) | S5 |
| Cam 1 (East)  | S6 |
| Cam 2 (South) | S7 |
| Cam 3 (West)  | S8 |

S1–S4 are signal-only poles on the opposite side of each intersection.

## Setup

### 1. Python side
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
# First run will auto-download yolov8s.pt (~22 MB)
python app.py
# Dashboard: http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

### 2. ESP32 side
1. Install Arduino IDE + ESP32 board package
2. Install libraries: `Blynk`, `ArduinoJson`
3. Open `esp32_traffic_controller.ino`
4. Fill in `WIFI_SSID`, `WIFI_PASS`, `BLYNK_TEMPLATE_ID`, `BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN`
5. Upload to ESP32
6. Open Serial Monitor @ 115200, note the assigned IP
7. Edit `communicator.py` → set `ESP32_IP` to that address

### 3. Blynk app
1. Create a template with name "SmartTraffic"
2. Add buttons V0–V7 (one per signal — "Force GREEN")
3. Add button V8 ("AUTO — release override")
4. Add the device, copy auth token into the `.ino`

## Tuning
| What | File | Knob |
|---|---|---|
| Ambulance sensitivity | `detector.py` | `RED_MIN_PIXELS`, `BLUE_MIN_PIXELS`, `FLASH_DELTA` |
| How long until accident | `accident.py` | `STATIONARY_THRESHOLD` |
| Movement tolerance | `accident.py` | `MOVEMENT_TOLERANCE` |
| Green time bounds | `signal_logic.py` | `MIN_GREEN_TIME`, `MAX_GREEN_TIME` |
| Yellow duration | `signal_logic.py` | `YELLOW_TIME` |
| Congestion threshold | `signal_logic.py` | `CONGESTION_LIMIT` |
| OCR frequency | `app.py` | `OCR_EVERY_N_CYCLES` |

## API
| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/status` | GET | Current full system state |
| `/api/plates` | GET | Last 20 plate captures |
| `/api/events` | GET | Last 15 events |
| `/api/search/<plate>` | GET | Trail for a specific plate |
| `/api/override/<cam>` | GET | Force GREEN on cam's signals |
| `/api/auto` | GET | Resume auto mode |
| `/api/allred` | GET | Emergency all-red |
| `/api/accident/<cam>` | GET | Manual accident report |
| `/api/accident_clear/<cam>` | GET | Clear manual accident |

## Known Limitations
- HSV ambulance detection depends on visible flashing lights — won't work
  for ambulances with steady (non-flashing) markings
- EasyOCR on CPU is slow; OCR runs every 3rd loop iteration by default
- Single ESP32 drives all 8 signals — for production, would use one ESP32
  per intersection
- 16 LEDs only (R+G). Yellow phase exists in logic and dashboard but is not
  physically shown. Switch to shift registers (74HC595) to add yellow LEDs.

